## Flag Help Template

For the `show_flag_help` action, use this extended template:

```
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{{PLUGIN_TITLE}} - Runtime Flags
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

DISPLAY FLAGS (control terminal output)
  --verbose, -v    Show all node details and condition evaluations
  --quiet, -q      Only user prompts and final result
  --terse          Batch summaries only (non-interactive nodes)
  --debug          Full state dumps after each node
  --no-display     Silent mode (no terminal output)

LOGGING FLAGS (control file logging)
  --log-level=X    Set logging level:
                     error  - Errors only
                     warn   - Warnings and errors
                     info   - Info, warnings, errors (default)
                     debug  - Debug level detail
                     trace  - Full execution trace
  --log-format=X   Output format: json, yaml, pretty
  --log-dir=X      Override log directory
  --trace          Shorthand for --log-level=trace
  --no-log         Disable all file logging
  --ci             CI mode: structured output, no progress

FLAG SCOPE
  Flags are per-invocation only. Example:
    /{{plugin_name}} --verbose analyze   <- verbose
    /{{plugin_name}} convert             <- normal (reset)

CONFIGURATION HIERARCHY
  1. Runtime flags (highest priority)
  2. Workflow initial_state
  3. Plugin .hiivmind/blueprint/display.yaml
  4. Framework defaults (lowest priority)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
```

